Cell["\<\
It\[CloseCurlyQuote]s a well known fact that half-wave layers have no effect \
on reflectance or transmittance of assemblies, at wavelengths at which they \
are truly half-wave. So we can have a window twice as thick:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7294395930148087`*^9, 3.7294395945810685`*^9}, {
